ops.insert: When using bioelectrical impedance for measuring body composition, why does an electrical current travel faster through muscle than it does through fat?

textDelta: When using bioelectrical impedance for measuring body composition, why does an electrical current travel faster through muscle than it does through fat? The electrical current travels faster through muscle than it does through fat because muscle is more conductive than fat.
